en 12-15 days fully off\t15 days/month guaranteed OFF = time for digital business Green Slip Economics\tPremium pay for open trips (typically 125-150% of normal rates)\tNYC has highest green slip frequency (weather, crew issues, connections)\t2-3 green slips/month = $2K-$4K additional income International Routes (NY-Caribbean)\tPuerto Rico, USVI, Dominican are international; pay international override + per diem\tLGA hub flies NY-SJU (San Juan) constantly; counts as international\tPer diem alone: $330-400/trip x 3-4 trips = $1,200-$1,600/month Per Diem Accumulation\tPaid tax-free while away from base (layovers count)\tReserve bidding = you pick overnights; layovers = per diem\t$2.25/hr per diem; on 4-hour flight + 18-hour layover = $50/trip minimum Aircraft Upgrade Path\tBy 2030, Endeavor fleet is newer (CRJ-900 → regional jets with automation)\tLess manual flying = less cognitive load; more time off-duty to handle digital business\tLess burnout; physical energy preserved for entrepreneurship DETAILED ENDEAVOR RESERVE + GREEN SLIP BIDDING STRATEGY Phase 1: Year 1-2 (Endeavor Air First Officer, Reserve) Timeline\tBidding Strategy\tExpected Block Hours/Month\tBase Pay Calculation\tPer Diem Income\tGreen Slip Bonus\tMonthly Total Income\tKey Actions Month 1-3\tIOE Training + safety protocols\t0-20 hours (partial)\t$105.08/hr × 10 hours = $1,050\t$0 (training mode)\t$0\t$1,050\tComplete initial training; learn bidding system Month 4-6\tBid: 36-day reserve block; zero green slip emphasis\t20-30 hours\t$105.08 × 25 = $2,627\t$2.25 × 25 hours = $56\t$0\t$2,683\tEstablish reliability; prove up on reserve Month 7-12\tBid: 36-day reserve + 2-3 green slips/month (premium trips)\t35-45 hours\t$105.08 × 40 = $4,203\t$2.25 × 50 hours layover = $112\tPremium pay: 125% × 3 trips = $1,575\t$5,890\tLearn green slip patterns; identify premium routes Year 2 (Months 13-24)\tStrategic: 36-day reserve + 4-6 green slips/month (international focus)\t50-65 hours\t$105.08 × 60 = $6,305\t$2.25 × 100 hours = $225\tInternational override: $4-6/hr + 150% × 5 trips = $3,200\t$9,730/month\tTarget NY-Puerto Rico, NY-Caribbean primarily Year 1 Total Income (Months 1-12): ~$48,500 (base + per diem + green slips) Year 2 Total Income: ~$116,760 (scaling green slip strategy) Phase 2: Year 3-4 (Endeavor Air First Officer → Captain Upgrade Path) Timeline\tBidding Strategy\tBlock Hours/Month\tBase Pay\tPer Diem\tGreen Slip + International Override\tMonthly Total\tAdvancement Notes Months 25-36\tAggressive: 36-day reserve + 6-8 green slips/month (seniority increasing)\t65-80 hours\t$108 × 70 = $7,560\t$2.25 × 120 hours = $270\tInternational routes earning $4.50/hr override + 150% × 6 trips = $4,800\t$12,630/month\tCaptain upgrade interview window opens; high seniority in reserve Months 37-48\tUpgrade to Endeavor Captain; transition from reserve to mixed schedule\t75-90 hours\tCaptain rate: $145 × 85 = $12,325\t$2.25 × 140 hours = $315\tInternational premium (captain): $6.50/hr override + 150% bonus = $5,200\t$17,840/month\tCaptain certification achieved; transition to line bidding option Year 3 Total Income: ~$151,560 Year 4 Total Income: ~$214,080 Critical Detail: How Reserve + Green Slip Economics Work Reserve Guarantee: You bid for a 36-day \"reserve block\" (on-call for 36 days) Minimum guarantee: 75 block hours/month (Endeavor contract) You're paid for the full 75 hours even if you fly 50 hours Per diem paid only when you're away from your domicile (on a trip) Green Slip Mechanics: Airline posts \"open trips\" (broken trips, crew swaps, weather cancellations) Green slips = 125-150% of normal hourly pay You can pick up green slips while on reserve International routes (NY-SJU, NY-Dominican) = additional $4-6.50/hr international override + per diem The Arbitrage: Reserve pilots get full monthly guarantee (75 hours) but only fly 40-50 actual hours. That 25-35 hour \"free credit\" = you pick premium green slips with higher per diem + international override without impacting your guarantee. NEW YORK TO PUERTO RICO: THE MONEY ROUTE Route\tFlight Time\tBlock Time\tLayover Duration\tPer Diem Earned\tInternational Override\tHourly Rate\tTotal Trip Income\tFrequency LGA-SJU (San Juan)\t4.0 hours\t4.5 hours\t18-24 hours (overnight)\t$2.25 × 22.5 = $50.62\t$4.50/hr × 4.5 = $20.25\t$105.08 × 4.5 = $472.86\t$543.73/trip\t3-4/month avg NYC-Cancun (via LGA/JFK routing)\t4.5 hours\t5.0 hours\t16-20 hours\t$2.25 × 18 = $"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"[Content truncated — view full chat at source URL]"}]},{"type":"paragraph","children":[{"text":"Source: "},{"type":"link","href":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=0324b307-d5f7-4065-b2de-4d1bd7aa84b5","children":[{"text":"https://www.genspark.ai/agents?id=0324b307-d5f7-4065-b2de-4d1bd7aa84b5"}]}]}]
